{"id": 243236342, "title": "ESPN\u2019s Dick Vitale diagnosed with cancer for 4th time; surgery scheduled for Tuesday", "text": "The 85-year-old Vitale has previously been treated for melanoma and lymphoma. He also had six weeks of radiation treatments last year when tests revealed he had vocal cord cancer. Vitale has been with ESPN since 1979, the year the network launched. The former coach called ESPN\u2019s first college basketball broadcast. He\u2019s also a longtime fundraiser for cancer research. Vitale helped friend Jim Valvano to the stage at the 1993 ESPYs, where Valvano delivered his famous \u201cDon\u2019t give up\u201d speech. Valvano died of adenocarcinoma less than two months later.", "summary": "BRISTOL, Conn. &#8212; Longtime ESPN college basketball analyst Dick Vitale said on social media he has been diagnosed with cancer for a fourth time. Vitale announced Friday that a biopsy of a lymph node in his neck showed cancer. He is scheduled to have surgery Tuesday. &#8220;With all the (prayers) I have received &#38; the [&#8230;]", "url": "https://torontosun.com/sports/basketball/espns-dick-vitale-diagnosed-with-cancer-for-4th-time-surgery-scheduled-for-tuesday", "image": "https://smartcdn.gprod.postmedia.digital/torontosun/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/espn-vitale-basketball.jpg?quality=100&strip=all", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-29 01:12:19", "author": "Associated Press", "authors": ["Associated Press"], "language": "en", "source_country": "CA", "sentiment": 0.075}